<br>
But as he walked towards the tent housing the commanders of the army, a beautiful blonde amazon caught his eye.  He grinned slightly, feeling more than a little bold, he approached her.  &quot;Good morning! May I assist you with your bags?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#993300>(5/31/03 1:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/188800.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dawning of a New Day</span><hr size=1> Kalasin turned quickly to the man that had approached her. She was used to men doing this sort of thing, but liked the look of this one, he seemed to have something that screamed power, and nothing made Kalasin Ti'Ya-Kuk'Tai more content in the company of someone. The young woman flashed a brilliant smile at him.<br>
&quot;If you would like.&quot; She replied politely, making sure that while she sounded innocent, she did not sound naïve. &quot;But I warn you, though they are not heavy, they can at times be rather… pointy.&quot;<br>
She chuckled briefly and then made eye contact with him, her emerald eyes shone in the light.<br>
&quot;I am Kalasin Ti'Ya-Kuk'Tai.&quot;<br>
The woman offered him a long nimble hand.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#993300>(5/31/03 10:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/ixltheseuslxl/myhomepage/theseus1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dawning of a New Day</span><hr size=1> Theseus nodded, thankful for her warning, &quot;I am Theseus of Themiscrya.&quot;  He extended his hand to her in greeting, unsure if he should offer a warriors handshake or not to the beauty before him.  But nonetheless, he took her long, nimble hand in his, caressing hers softly as his eyes were captured by hers.  &quot;I will keep your words in mind then.  May I ask where you are headed and may I have the honor of escorting you there?&quot;  He picked up her bags as their eyes made contact and he smiled at her a little embarrassed at the attraction he felt towards this woman.  His brow arching slightly, the bags were not heavy at all.  He shifted them slightly and then began to walk with her.  &quot;Will you be staying in Troy long?&quot;  He glanced at her as they walked, grateful for the diversion of her company. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#993300>(6/1/03 1:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/188800.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dawning of a New Day</span><hr size=1> &quot;This is my first time inside of Troy actually&quot; she said somewhat cheerfully. &quot;So really, I have no clue where I am heading, or what I am going to do once I am there.&quot;<br>
She had to admit that she liked this man. He was definitely easy to look at, and one of the more polite men that she had met. Most of the men that she met nowadays were interesting in nothing more than ogling at her.<br>
&quot;You know when you get the urge to visit a place for the simple reason that you have not been there before?&quot; her thick accent at times made her speech a little hard to comprehend, but for the most part it was rather clear. &quot;Well, that is the urge that brought me to Troy.&quot;<br>
She looked at him again, always the one to make eye contact when talking to people.<br>
&quot;Themisycra you say? Are you related to any of the amazons there?&quot;<br>
Though her eyes were almost in constant contact with either his own eyes or his form, she continued to successfully weave through any obstacles in her path without looking to the ground. Judging by the way in which he carried her things, he did not find them heavy at all. She made a mental note that he was a strong man, much stronger than herself.<br>
&quot;Where is a good place to head if you do not mind my asking?&quot; she paused and grimaced. &quot;I speak too much don't I?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#993300>(6/1/03 10:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Blind Leading the Blind</span><hr size=1> Theseus listened to her as she spoke.  She was talkative and that was a good thing.  It meant she wasn't afraid of saying too much.  He smiled at her as he glanced at her sideways.  &quot;You speak well and the accent, well, it only makes your speech that much more enrapturing to listen to.&quot;  He led her through the street, weaving through some of the street vendors and their patrons as they went.  &quot;I am staying at the tavern just near the middle of the city until I can afford to get my own place.  You are more than welcome to stay there with me or if that makes you  uncomfortable, we could see about getting you a room in the tavern.  That way if you needed anything, perhaps I could help you out.&quot;  For now his trip to enlist in the Trojan army was forgotten.  He was helping the lady and that's really all that matter.  Upon her questioning his relationship with the amazons of Themiscrya, he tensed slightly. He did not want to simply be known as the son of Hippolyte or the son of Gabrielle.  He wanted to be indentified as his own man, yet he did not want to be dishonest with this fair maiden either.  He nodded, &quot;Yes, I was born in the amazon village of Themiscrya.&quot; He glanced at her, he could feel her eyes on him and the almost constant eye contact was only further peaking his interest in this girl. His mother's warnings rang through his mind, and he urged himself to maintain his self control and not make a total ass of himself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#993300>(6/1/03 8:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Just Following Along</span><hr size=1> Kalasin nodded when he spoke, and visibly brightened when he said that she could stay with him for a time. It could quite possibly save her a lot of grief, given that she was extremely good at saying the wrong thing that the wrong time. It was a talent that she had inherited from her mother, along with her looks.<br>
“That sounds wonderful” she said, smiling all the while. “I doubt that someone as decent as you could make me feel uncomfortable.”<br>
It was true, with all that she had gone through in her life, she doubted that him turning out to be the spawn of an evil demonic goat would make her feel slightly uncomfortable. Though, she was rather eager to learn more about him, he seemed like an incredibly interesting individual.<br>
“I am amazed though. People do not often like my accent, apparently it makes me hard to comprehend at times. Though, I think that is just my lousy Greek.” She chuckled. “It’s a hard language to get your tongue around.”<br>
The young woman decided that she would drop the subject of Themisycra, obviously he did not want to talk about it, not that it bothered her in the slightest. There were plenty of other things that she could talk about with him.<br>
“So Theseus, what were you planning on doing today?” Her emerald eyes looked slightly worried, like she feared that she had distracted him from something more important. “I hope that I didn’t distract you from it…”<br>
Kalasin was quite shocked. Normally she would not have cared a thing about anyone. She wondered if the man knew just who he was talking to. She was a highly regarded warrior woman, and a highly ranked amazon. As a former amazon princess, head ambassador of Themisycra, Personal Advisor to the queen of the Shaotmlic amazons and the Head Assassin of the Crimson Valley, she was no stranger to burdens, and tried herself to leave them out of conversation. Much like him, she did not wished to be judged by her titles, and even less by her past deeds.<br>
