<br>
He opened the tavern door and led her inside.  &quot;Just follow me, my quarters are right up the stairs and down the hallway.&quot;  He led her to the stairs and then up, ignoring the whistles that came as a result of her entrance into the tavern.  He'd found that at this point it was always better to simply ignore the ignorance of others and proceed on his way.  He stopped in front of the door and slid the key into the lock, pushing open the door. He held the door open for her, letting her enter first.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/03 12:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just Following Along</span><hr size=1> Kalasin raised an eyebrow at the man that whistled at her. As she walked past one, she discreetly sent a fist into his right temple, knocking him out straight away. His friends stopped their teasing almost instantly. The young amazon looked back briefly and smiled at them.<br>
She nodded her thanks to Theseus and entered the room.  It was a nice enough place, not one that she would want to live in for an extended period of time, but nice none the less. She turned back to Theseus and smiled.<br>
&quot;I call the floor.&quot; She said innocently and stood still for a moment, unsure of what to do.<br>
Had she been in possession of her bag, she would have unpacked it, or done something with it. But seeing as she was standing there with nothing in her arms, she really had nothing to do.<br>
&quot;I must admit, I have never seen the Trojan Army in action. I have heard good things about them though.&quot; She said quickly. Her speech was always quick to cover for small errors that she often made when speaking the tongue. &quot;My husband saw them in battle once, he tells me they are quite brilliant at what they do.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/03 5:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/ixltheseuslxl/myhomepage/theseus1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just Following Along</span><hr size=1> Theseus tensed slightly again as he placed her bag up on the bed, &quot;No, you can have the bed and I will take the cot that folds out of that wall.  Noone has to sleep on the floor.&quot;  He was not sure that it was safe to be sharing quarters with a married woman.  He only hoped that her husband would be a reasonable man should he follow her to Troy.  He released her bags and stepped back slightly to give her room.  <br>
<br>
His mother had warned him countless times about things of this nature.  Should he piss off a jealous husband he was certain to be on his own and he was not looking forward to that experience anytime soon.  &quot;Perhaps I should leave you to your things.  You are probably quite tired after your journey and I should go tend to my business.&quot;  He ran his fingers through his hair nervously.  &quot;Just make yourself at home here.&quot;  He smiled slightly, keeping his eyes off of her.  She belonged to another and he was not about to violate those vows that she'd taken. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/03 8:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.speedis.org/images/214.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Just who is this girl?</span><hr size=1> Kalasin smiled widely when she noticed that he had tensed so much since her mention of Hiroshi Yamamoto. She closed her eyes for a moment and took a deep breathe. This happened far too often for her liking. She walked over to him and put a hand on his shoulder.<br>
<br>
&quot;Theseus, please, do you truly think that my husband is going to come after you for being a good friend to me?&quot; the young woman sighed, she did not want him to think that he would be in any trouble, he would not. &quot;My Greek is poor. In the tongue I am most fluent in, I would call him my zensha shujin. Husband of the before I think is pretty close to what you would say.&quot;<br>
<br>
She didn't want him to feel uncomfortable around her, the amazon woman got that too much already. Quickly, she turned to the back and emptied it out on the bed. Various nasty looking weapons fell out, along with some clothing. She shrugged, making sure that she still had everything, and then turned back to Theseus.<br>
<br>
&quot;You don't have to worry about him. We are no longer engaged in a formal wedlock. Also, he is a man with a wonderful temper. He couldn't hurt a fly if he tried.&quot;<br>
<br>
That wasn't completely true. She had seen what he could do if someone hurt her at all. But then again, since their meeting when she was only fourteen, eight years ago, that had only happened once. The amazon shifted uncomfortably in her travel dress. As she spoke, she rummaged through the few clothes that she had until she found a white chiton that reached the middle of her thigh. She smiled upon finding it, and without hesitation, pulled her current dress over her head, not ashamed of her nakedness, tossed it onto the bed, took the chiton, and put it on.<br>
The amazon, now comfortable, turned back to Theseus.<br>
<br>
&quot;Seriously, I only speak the truth. I don't want you to treat me any differently because I happen to have a man back in Hyrcania okay? I am not a different person. Just like you are not a different person because you were raised in Themisycra. You know what I mean?&quot;<br>
<br>
Finally, she sat down on the bed, frowning as she did so.<br>
<br>
&quot;Actually, I think I may sleep on the floor.&quot; she smiled sweetly. &quot;This bed is really quite nasty.&quot; When she noticed that he virtually refused to look at her, she sighed again, this time rather sadly. &quot;You can look at me you know. It is not a sin. You think my body is on display by accident?&quot; <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=battlingangel>Battling Angel</A> at: 6/2/03 8:27:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#993300>(6/2/03 9:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm65.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/ixltheseuslxl/myhomepage/theseus1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just who is this girl?</span><hr size=1> Theseus jaw dropped lightly when she changed unashamed in front of him.  It wasn't that he'd never seen a girl semi-nude before, on the contrary, he had, but never one like that.  He swallowed hard and walked as calmly as possible over to the wash basin.  He dipped his hands into the cool water and then splashed his face.  Not even bothering with a towel, the turned to her, &quot;I do not know why your body is on display.  It is not business of mine when you belong to another why you choose to dress as you do or behave as you do.  It is sacred, the vows you took.  I will not go against the laws and the blessings of Hera. There are certain bonds that should never be severed no matter what the temptation.&quot;<br>
